

class Leg(self, name, h_shoulder_servo, v_shoulder_servo, knee_servo)

Description:
  The purpose is to encapsulate the related servos and coordinate their operation.
 
Member Variables:
  name - name of the leg ("Front Right Leg")
  h_shoulder_servo - horizontal shoulder servo
  v_shoulder_servo - vertical shoulder servo
  knee_servo
  
Methods:
  def __init__(self, name, h_shoulder_servo, v_shoulder_servo, knee_servo)
    - assigns arguments to their respective member variables
  def step(direction)
    - Steps this individual leg forward if [direction is 1], [backward if direction is -1] by coordinating the 3 servos. 
    - Also emits a message "(name) stepping forward".
